Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.72,0:00:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.65,0:00:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worried that this full tank of energy will lose it's destination
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.90,0:00:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whoever shakes for just a minute their boredom, will explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.04,0:00:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I ride, atop the white line, Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.14,0:00:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sit down, in the place you have faith Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.15,0:00:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go to the place that tempts you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.50,0:00:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If each person took one thing at a time, freedom and passion in their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.83,0:00:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the shine to come, continue our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.97,0:00:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unclear everyday trump-card that sustains me, is your soul
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The best growth is coming forth, unstoppable wild drive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.21,0:01:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We are both yet to settle down, striking the door
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.18,0:01:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Counterattack! Gilford the Lightning"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.23,0:01:28.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn...! My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.40,0:01:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.19,0:01:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Jounouchi's Monster has\N 3000 Attack Points,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.36,0:01:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he should be able to attack and\N beat Malik in an instant, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.61,0:01:40.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True... Malik doesn't have any\N Wall Monsters on the field right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.16,0:01:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that is likely\N just what Malik planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.33,0:01:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no doubt that his\N reverse card is a Trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.50,0:01:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I gotta do something\N about his obvious Trap first!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.80,0:01:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right! Hurricane!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.09,0:02:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please! Please draw Hurricane!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.51,0:02:01.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.26,0:02:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't have any more\N Monster Cards in my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What do I do...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.69,0:02:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The problem is his Trap Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.23,0:02:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if he uses it to block my attack, it should go to the Graveyard after he uses it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.69,0:02:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But still...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.03,0:02:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Provided that, of course,\N the player can handle his red-hot body\N melting around him every turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.20,0:02:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and taking 700 points of\N damage every turn as a result!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.70,0:02:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I guess you could say\N this Monster is quite a handful!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.95,0:02:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}700 points every turn...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.37,0:02:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go screw yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.67,0:02:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I just sit here and do nothing,\N my Life will continue to drop...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.63,0:02:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So I'll step into your trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.55,0:02:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.72,0:02:42.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll attack you with your little\N grotesque pet just like you wanted!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.43,0:02:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really~?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.47,0:02:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd be too scared of my\N face-down to try and attack me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.44,0:02:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.14,0:02:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you have quite a good hunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.23,0:03:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Just as you figured, this Trap does not have a permanent effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.03,0:03:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will disappear from\N the field on my next turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.91,0:03:07.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck? Malik just {\i1}told{\i0}\N Jounouchi that he has a Trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.24,0:03:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it... He's making fun of him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.79,0:03:15.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even {\b0}I{\b1} don't know what will happen if you fire\N this hot-headed deadbeat up too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.46,0:03:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not even Kaiba Corporation's\N most advanced computer systems
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.97,0:03:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}would be able to predict\N the way he thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.09,0:03:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My pet's ultimate attack\N is called "Golem Volcano"!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.68,0:03:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me hear you shout it\N nice and loud, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.68,0:03:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's {\b0}my{\b1} Monster,\N so {\b0}I'll{\b1} name it's attacks!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack, Lava Golem!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.73,0:03:36.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi Fire!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.44,0:03:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,J-Jounouchi Fire, he said...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.73,0:03:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,G-Good one! Now go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.44,0:03:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi Fire's really cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.74,0:03:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse Trap activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.83,0:03:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like {\i1}that{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.87,0:03:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster Relief!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.87,0:03:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It activates when the\N opposing player declares an attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.84,0:03:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The card lets me return\N one Monster to my hand
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.67,0:04:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Special Summon a\N Four-Star Monster to take its place!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.88,0:04:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His {\i1}own{\i0} Monster...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.89,0:04:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Malik doesn't have a\N Monster of his own on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.31,0:04:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he has the Plasma Eel that's\N been causing Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s\N Panther Warrior all its suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.19,0:04:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I return Plasma Eel to my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.73,0:04:20.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll then Summon Plasma Eel\N again in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.91,0:04:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plasma Eel won't be destroyed\N in battle by {\i1}any{\i0} Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.42,0:04:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it all..!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.83,0:04:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now Helpoemer will kill off\N another card from your hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.88,0:04:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.43,0:04:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}now{\i0}... Lava Golem's\N red-hot body will begin to {\i1}melt{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.52,0:04:58.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...taking some of your \N{\i1}Life{\i0} along with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.98,0:05:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So {\i1}hot{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.53,0:05:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How {\i1}unsightly{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.78,0:05:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Another Dark Game is\N being played this very moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.54,0:05:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will Malik's dark side not be satisfied\N until he destroys himself
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.83,0:05:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and sends everyone\N else to the darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.46,0:05:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.13,0:05:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Machine Reproduction Technique, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.88,0:05:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Using this, I'll paralyze him for {\b0}real{\b1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.01,0:05:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card\N Machine Reproduction Technique!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.39,0:05:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Machine Reproduction Technique?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.35,0:05:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I have a Machine-Type Monster with\N 500 Attack Points or less on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.23,0:05:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can Special Summon up to two Monsters holding the same name from your deck...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.07,0:05:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...using this Magic Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.90,0:05:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:55.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My deck includes two {\i1}more{\i0}\N Plasma Eels, you see!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.75,0:05:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out! Plasma Eel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.67,0:06:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!? There's three\N Plasma Eels on the field?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.59,0:06:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using their Special Power, they attach\N themselves to the enemy Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.98,0:06:23.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.94,0:06:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's{\i0} the sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.28,0:06:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me hear {\i1}more screams{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many more turns\N can you keep this up, Jounouchi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.54,0:06:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... damn nut job...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.67,0:06:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, I place two\N face-down cards and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.80,0:06:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it goes on like this,\N Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0} will...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.39,0:06:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit...! Can't he do something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.23,0:07:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As I thought, there was no reason to call God for a worthless deadbeat like him...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.15,0:07:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yugi... Isn't there\N something Jounouchi can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.49,0:07:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1} only\N has one card left in his hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.95,0:07:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But there has to be\N a way in that one card.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.04,0:07:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't give up.\N Believe in your hand until the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.25,0:07:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As long as this Lava Golem is on my field,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.63,0:07:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}my Life Points will continue to be drained every turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.76,0:07:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I don't do something\N about this thing, I'll lose...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.76,0:07:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But the only card I've got\N in my hand is the Angel Dice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.35,0:07:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.15,0:07:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! I promised I'd\N Duel Yugi in the Final!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.57,0:07:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't afford to lose here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.53,0:07:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll believe in the next card\N I draw from my deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.28,0:07:56.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.95,0:07:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gilford the Lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.91,0:08:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to sacrifice two Monsters on my field\N in order to Summon an Eight-Star Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.88,0:08:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I can't sacrifice a Monster\N the Plasma Eel is attached to...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.63,0:08:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And just Panther Warrior\N by himself won't be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.68,0:08:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wait a sec...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.43,0:08:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's still a way...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.43,0:08:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.43,0:08:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Angel Dice!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.68,0:08:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Angel Dice lets me increase the\N Attack Points of a Monster with\N less than 500 Attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.90,0:08:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Continuous Magic,\N Machine Reproduction Technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.49,0:08:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can only make Machine-Type Monsters\N with less than 500 Attack Points, {\i1}right{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.83,0:08:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it!\N Brilliant strategy, Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.25,0:08:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I wonder what's gonna\N happen if I raise the Attack Power\N of the Plasma Eel on your field!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.52,0:09:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plasma Eel's Attack Points\N multiply by six!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.02,0:09:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From 500 to 3000 points\N in a single stroke!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.27,0:09:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}that{\i0} means the Continuous Magic Card,\N Machine Reproduction Technique, is destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.90,0:09:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That also means the two\N Plasma Eels leeching onto\N my Monsters are destroyed along with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.41,0:09:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I got my three sacrifices!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.96,0:09:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.92,0:09:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice three Tributes -\N Lava Golem, Rocket Warrior\N and Panther Warrior...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.47,0:09:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to Summon Gilford the Lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.03,0:10:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This guy is gonna end\N your miserable life!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.28,0:10:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So get ready, Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.80,0:10:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'cha think?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.84,0:10:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the toughest servant\N I got in my deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.47,0:10:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The legendary warrior\N who controls the storm!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.01,0:10:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gonna take you down, Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.77,0:10:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.73,0:10:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He Summoned a\N High-Level Monster with ease!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.64,0:10:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He turned the tables!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.69,0:10:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sick him, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.99,0:10:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell's so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.61,0:10:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fool to no end...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.53,0:10:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just raised the Attack\N of my Plasma Eel to 3000!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.54,0:10:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's got 200 more Attack Points than\N your Gilford the Lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.13,0:10:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the "legendary warrior" you worked\N so hard to Summon will die in vain!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.38,0:11:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're{\i0} the foolish one here, Malik-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.26,0:11:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.22,0:11:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Gilford the Lighting is\N sacrificed with {\i1}three{\i0} Monsters,\N his Special Ability activates.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.31,0:11:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on and {\i1}show{\i0} him, Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.69,0:11:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.32,0:11:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gilford the Lighting's\N Special Ability activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.40,0:11:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lighting Thunder!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.95,0:11:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.12,0:11:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plasma Eel, who's supposed to not be able\N to be destroyed in battle, was {\i1}beaten{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.50,0:11:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a {\i1}battle{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.59,0:11:39.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a {\i1}Special Ability{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.38,0:11:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Gilford the Lighting is Summoned,\N it instantly destroys all Monsters on\N the opponent's side of the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.39,0:11:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter {\i1}what{\i0} kinds of\N Special Powers those Monsters may have!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.93,0:11:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alrighty! You just lost all the\N Monsters on your field!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.15,0:11:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get your ass ready, Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.32,0:11:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Direct Attack with\N Gilford the Lightning!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.82,0:12:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lightning Crash Sword!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.61,0:12:06.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this attack goes through, I win!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think I'd {\i1}let{\i0} you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.29,0:12:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse Trap, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.29,0:12:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nightmare Mirror!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.50,0:12:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Jounouchi, I guess you deserve\N a hand for lasting this long...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.88,0:12:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But playtime has {\i1}long{\i0} past!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.39,0:12:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What?! I can see\N my reflection in the mirror...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.01,0:12:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! And Gilford the Lightning is going\N to attack {\i1}you{\i0} inside the mirror!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.16,0:12:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen carefully, Jounouchi...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.91,0:12:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attacking the mirror inflicts 1000\N points of damage to your Life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.92,0:13:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, I too must accept some risk\N by discarding a card from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.71,0:13:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll send this card to the Graveyard...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.43,0:13:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Helpoemer's Effect will now send a\N card in your hand to the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.06,0:13:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd {\i1}love{\i0} to say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.85,0:13:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but there's no helping it,\N since you don't even {\i1}have{\i0} a hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.19,0:13:19.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}By the way Malik's acting...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.27,0:13:22.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...he must be planning\N something next turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.94,0:13:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is he {\b0}finally{\b1} going to play it...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.40,0:13:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.99,0:13:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He doesn't have a Monster or a reverse card on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.74,0:13:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I can just get through this turn, I'll win!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.54,0:13:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn. Draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.25,0:13:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell? Quit the creepy laughing\N and just get on with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:49.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I admit that I've\N underestimated you a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.18,0:13:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never would have imagined\N that I would need to use God\M against the likes of {\i1}you{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.27,0:13:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.73,0:13:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Winged Sun Dragon of Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.31,0:14:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ra's Attack Power is determined\N by the Monsters sacrificed in\N order to Summon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is there a way to Summon it\N without sacrificing while still\N maintaining Attack Points?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.24,0:14:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!\N Is he going to Summon the god?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.50,0:14:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Here, in the battlefield of this\N Semi-Final match, you've become\N a sacrifice, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.04,0:14:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In order for me to learn more about Ra!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.71,0:14:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After this turn, I'll finally learn all \Nof Ra's Hidden Special Powers!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.76,0:14:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}According to the Hieratic Text\N I deciphered on the God Card...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's first Ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.14,0:14:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ra shall take power\N from three sacrifices...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.23,0:14:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, even if the sacrifices are to the god's liking,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.36,0:14:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the god shall only answer to the one\N who speaks the sacred spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.73,0:14:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And its second Ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.11,0:14:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}God shall come forth from the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...when one chants the spell that\N grants it the means of resurrection.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.08,0:14:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Those who face it in war shall be\N incinerated by flames in an instant\N and burned to a corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.13,0:15:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And as for its third Ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.13,0:15:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In an instant,\N God shall become a phoenix.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.63,0:15:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And all its enemies\N shall return to the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.97,0:15:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.80,0:15:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resurrection of the Dead!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.52,0:15:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now behold God!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.69,0:15:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.50,0:15:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He Summoned Ra with\N Resurrection of the Dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.51,0:15:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it will have 0 Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.63,0:15:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, Magic Cards only affect\N a god for one turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.14,0:16:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it {\i1}was{\i0} Special Summoned,\N it should go back to the Graveyard\N before it can even attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what you're thinking,\N but Ra has the power of Swift Attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.69,0:16:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now the third \NAbility of Ra activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.40,0:16:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell's he up to now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.36,0:16:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ra's being covered in flames!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.95,0:16:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's changing form!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.66,0:16:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Winged Sun Dragon - Final Form!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.37,0:16:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,GOD PHOENIX!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.08,0:16:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,G-God Phoenix...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.04,0:16:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's completely different\N from the time it beat Mai...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.34,0:16:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought I would have to show\N {\i1}you{\i0} the true nature of Ra...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.64,0:16:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can be {\i1}proud{\i0} of that, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.93,0:16:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.35,0:16:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is Ra's final form?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.85,0:16:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is the {\i1}end{\i0}, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.19,0:16:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}die{\i0} this turn!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.19,0:16:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is this disturbing feeling...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.24,0:16:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I feel like something really bad\N is about to happen to my brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.33,0:17:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ishizu-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.75,0:17:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you... not going to watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.26,0:17:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your elder brother won, did he not?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.09,0:17:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.34,0:17:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to be here with Mai-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.69,0:17:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's been with me up until now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.11,0:17:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.11,0:17:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he beats this person named Malik,\N Mai-{\i1}san{\i0} will return to normal, won't she...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.95,0:17:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My big brother is the one who is\N Dueling that Malik this very moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.16,0:17:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Katsuya Jounouchi is the one\N fighting in that Dark Game...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.13,0:17:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My big brother is fighting\N in order to save Mai-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.55,0:17:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that is why I want to do everything\N I can to help Mai-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.64,0:18:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.47,0:18:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am doing everything I am capable of doing,\N now that I have lost the power\N of the Millennium Tauk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.69,0:18:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All I can do is hope that someone\N defeats Malik's dark personality...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.32,0:18:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and in order to get Rishid\N to regain consciousness...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.65,0:18:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I can do nothing but remain by his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.07,0:18:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, one woman is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.41,0:18:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ishizu-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.45,0:18:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will watch over her for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.54,0:18:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So move along.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.04,0:18:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.46,0:18:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}are{\i0} worried about\N your older brother, are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.47,0:18:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So hurry up and go to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.39,0:18:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take care of Mai-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.11,0:18:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A Dark Game is a game of death...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.15,0:19:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It is very likely that\N while you watch his fight...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.24,0:19:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...all that awaits you is a\N cruel memory you will hope to forget...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.33,0:19:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.42,0:19:11.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Despite that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.21,0:19:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1\b0}Because{\b1} you are his only sibling...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.30,0:19:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...you have to accept whatever the\N outcome may be and fight alongside him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.51,0:19:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All because you are his only sibling...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.94,0:19:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When Ra is Special Summoned\N with Resurrection of the Dead,\N it should have 0 Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.53,0:19:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But Malik just declared he will\N defeat Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1} this turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.86,0:19:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Does that mean Ra possesses an\N even {\b0}more{\b1} terrifying hidden power?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.12,0:19:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.33,0:19:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.83,0:19:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's thanks to Jounouchi that you both\N will see a preview of Ra's final form!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.88,0:19:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you send him off\N with a big round of applause!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.42,0:20:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make it loud enough for this pitiful Duelist\N to hear you all the way down in {\i1}Hell{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.68,0:20:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why {\i1}you{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.01,0:20:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go writing me off that easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still have Gilford the Lighting,\N with 2800 Attack Points, on my field!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.35,0:20:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can beat me with\N God's 0 Attack Points, go on and show me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.65,0:20:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just be {\i1}quiet{\i0} and\N wait for death, Jounouchi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.91,0:20:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After you bare witness to\N God's third Hidden Special Ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.62,0:20:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you will be wandering the pits of Hell,\N with the most painful sensation on Earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.33,0:20:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? A Special Ability?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.00,0:20:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ra's Third Hidden Power...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.80,0:20:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I pay 1000 of my Life Points,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.01,0:20:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it {\i1}incinerates{\i0}\N the Monsters on the field...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.97,0:20:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...no matter {\i1}how strong{\i0}\N their Attack Value!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.43,0:20:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}H-He can kill Gilford the Lighting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.85,0:20:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, even if you're able to use its\N Special Power to destroy\N the Monsters on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.77,0:20:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you still won't be able\N to lower my Life Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.65,0:21:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning you {\i1}can't{\i0}\N defeat me on this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.65,0:21:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.24,0:21:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Duel is a {\i1}Dark Game{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.12,0:21:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The players feel the {\i1}same sensations{\i0}\N their Monsters feel!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.17,0:21:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.58,0:21:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God's judgment will burn both your\N {\i1}mind and body{\i0} into ashes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.47,0:21:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Regardless{\i0} of whether\N you have Life Points left,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.05,0:21:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all that awaits you\N is {\i1}death and defeat{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.72,0:21:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.47,0:21:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the phoenix rises for you alone,\N to lead you into the darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.52,0:21:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Phoenix!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.98,0:21:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.86,0:21:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the Winged Sun Dragon of Ra's Special Ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.19,0:21:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if Gilford the Lighting is destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.78,0:21:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi's life energy will burn up along with his Monster because of the Dark Game!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.03,0:21:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't die, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.29,0:21:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you fall now,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how will you keep your promise to Mai-{\i1}san{\i0} to give her courage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.50,0:21:58.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have some of your Life left!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.00,0:22:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you make it through this,\N you can beat Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.50,0:22:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Jounouchi Falls"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.38,0:22:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.30,0:22:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, wherever it rises
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.20,0:22:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A dream is a dream, and it won't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.54,0:22:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The straight rail and the steep route
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.15,0:22:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To go, or not go all of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.54,0:22:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm getting tired of counting my advances in a cage
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.10,0:22:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Respect! Boys, show me your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.72,0:22:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's awkward, but draw the map
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.48,0:22:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now let's walk forever with our head up high...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.57,0:23:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, if it starts to get to familiar like you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.49,0:23:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}answer freely to the everyday discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.22,0:23:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to believe you, because I am losing my way with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.18,0:23:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hiding in my heart... this secret paradise
